sources.description:
Two Worlds Collide in the Wild West's Untamed Heart!
"King of Sierras" is a unique cinematic venture, blending original footage with additional scenes to weave a tale of the untamed American West. As ranchers battle wild mustangs amidst the backdrop of dust storms and drought, a young rancher's son finds himself entangled in a clash of cultures and a quest for survival.

Original title: King of the Sierras (1938) AKA Killers of the Prairie / Black Stallion

Colorized version: https://youtu.be/2-xzlB2DmLo


Directors: Samuel Diege, Arthur Rosson
Writers: Scott Darling, Paul Franklin, Frank Gay
Actors: Rex, Hobart Bosworth, Harry Harvey Jr.
Genres: Western, Drama
